---
import '../styles/main.css';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Solutions — eLife Pathways</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <PageHero pageTitle="Solutions" pageHeading="Infrastructure for the open science ecosystem">
      <p>The greatest untapped potential lies in the connections between the different parts of the scholarly publishing ecosystem. By creating interoperable, open-source tools we can enable communities to work together in ways that weren't previously possible.</p>
      <p>Our development of open infrastructure lies in co-publishing. By prioritising consistent management and interoperability we facilitate existing open publishing and pave the way for high quality, performance-driven solutions for the publishing community.</p>
      <figure>
        <img src="/images/solutions-placeholder.png" alt="" />
      </figure>
    </PageHero>

    <main>

      <section class="content-section" data-theme="navy">
        <div class="[ wrapper ] [ flow ]">
          <h2>Open Publishing</h2>
          <p>Our development of ArticleViewer and other tools creates an open network for multi-format publishing, including preprints. By enabling consistent management and interoperability we facilitate existing open publishing and pave the way for high quality, performance-driven solutions for the publishing community.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section" data-theme="purple">
        <div class="[ wrapper ] [ flow ]">
          <h2>Preprints and early sharing</h2>
          <p>We have developed and maintain the infrastructure for preprint sharing and early research communication. Our tools support communities in making research available sooner, enabling faster discovery and feedback across the scholarly ecosystem.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section" data-theme="navy">
        <div class="[ wrapper ] [ flow ]">
          <h2>Review and curation</h2>
          <p>We provide the infrastructure for modern research sharing, including preprint review and the publish-review-curate (PRC) model. By decoupling evaluation from publishing, our tools give communities autonomy over the review process. <a href="#">Kotahi</a> enables integrated custom review and evaluation workflows. <a href="#">Sciety</a> aggregates review and evaluation across scholarly networks, providing the tools to discover and organise all curated objects across the entire research ecosystem.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section" data-theme="purple">
        <div class="[ wrapper ] [ flow ]">
          <h2>Open Research Information</h2>
          <p>We specialise in open research information and scholarly metadata. Because a thriving open science ecosystem depends on robust connections, we enrich and enhance scholarly metadata to create seamless links between research outputs, rapidly prototyping new ways to showcase open research innovation.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section" data-theme="navy">
        <div class="[ wrapper ] [ flow ]">
          <h2>Expertise on open-source software delivery</h2>
          <p>We help navigate the complexities of open-source development with technical guidance and community-focused expertise. Whether launching a new innovation or adopting an existing tool, we work alongside the community to create a culture of agility and shared ownership, ensuring research technology delivers immediate and lasting value to the scholarly community.</p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>
